<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9856526372902></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9856526372902><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9856526372902>RE: Twisting and customized socials</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9856526372902#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 26th 7:23 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;True Philo. I have programmed a social to handle twisting of three songs. It is a great theory but can be very costly in a tough fight. If any one of the songs gets interupted or misses a note then the cycle is lost and the social keeps going. So IE. if the total time to twist 3 songs is 8 sec. then if the first song misses a note then you are stuck waiting for the whole 8 sec. until the programmed social is completed. The social will continue even though a song has failed. This can be a disaster for you soloing and could get your groupmates pretty angry if not killed. I advise not to use this until EQ has changed the way we program socials.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
